{
  "text": "which is exactly the dimension of P k (K). Therefore, it suffices to show that v \u2208 P k (K) vanishes if it vanishes at all the degrees of freedom. It is readily seen that the trace of v| F \u2208 P k (F ), which has to be zero since the degrees of freedom on the face are that of 2D Argyris elements [CITATION_1] (this also shows the C 0 -continuity on face). Therefore v = b K p for some p \u2208 P k\u22124 (K), where b K is the quartic volume bubble function. By the set of degrees of freedom on element K, we deduce v \u2261 0. The C 1 -continuity on the edge follows from the C 1 -continuity of 2D Argyris elements.",
